Module it.polimi.ingsw.PSP30

Package it.polimi.ingsw.PSP30.Messages

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BlockRemovalRequest
    Implements the request of removing a block.
    BlockRemovalResponse
    Implements the message sending to server the coordinates of the space from which to remove a block.
    BuildRequest
    Implements the message asking the player to build.
    BuildResponse
    Implements the message sending to server the coordinates where to move the selectedWorker.
    ChoseGodRequest
    Implements the message asking the player the god he will use during the game.
    ChoseGodResponse
    Implements the answer to ChoseGodRequest message.
    Disconnection
    Implements disconnection implements the notification message after the disconnection.
    GameStartNotification
    Implements the start game notification.
    GameStatusNotification
    Notifies the users about the current state of the game.
    GodsListRequest
    Implements the message sending to the challenger the list of gods and asks him to choose which of them will be used in the game.
    GodsListResponse
    Sends to the server the list of gods the challenger has chosen to play with.
    InvalidGodError
    Implements the message which warns the player the god he has chosen isn't valid.
    InvalidMoveError
    Implements the message which warns the player the move he has selected isn't valid.
    InvalidStarterPlayerError
    Implements the message which warns the player whom has chosen the starter opponent, that the selected opponent isn't valid.
    InvalidWorkerError
    Implements the message which warns the player the worker he has chosen isn't valid.
    LastGodNotification
    Implements the message which notifies the last player that has remained only one god and it will be his card.
    LobbyStatusNotification
    Sends to the player waiting for a new game the actual status of the lobby.
    Message
    Abstract class implementing the messages that will be sent between Server and Client.
    MoveRequest
    Implements the message sending to player the possible moves of the selectedWorker and asks the coordinates of the destination space.
    MoveResponse
    Implements the message sending to server the coordinates where to move the selectedWorker.
    NoPossibleMoveError
    Implements the message which warns the player the move he has chosen isn't possible.
    NumPlayersRequest
    Asks the player the type of the game he wants to play (two or three players).
    NumPlayersResponse
    Sends to the server the type of game the player wants to play.
    OtherWorkerMoveRequest
    Implements the request of moving the other worker.
    PingMessage
    Implements the message of ping.
    PlayerDisconnectedError
    Implements the message which warns the player that one of his opponents has left the game.
    SelectWorkerRequest
    Implements the message asking the player the worker he wants to move during the Move phase of the turn.
    SelectWorkerResponse
    Implements the message sending to server the worker the player wants to move.
    StartPlayerRequest
    Implements the message sending to the challenger the list of player and asks who will be the first player to make the move.
    StartPlayerResponse
    Implements the message sending to the server the first player of the game.
    UsePowerRequest
    Implements the message which asks the player if he wants to use the power of his card.
    UsePowerResponse
    Implements the message sent with the choice of the player to use the power or not.
    UsernameRequest
    Used by server to ask player's username after accepting the connection.
    UsernameResponse
    Used for sending to the server the player's username.
    UsernameTakenError
    Implements the message which alerts the player the username he has chosen isn't valid.
    WinnerNotification
    Implements the message used to announce the winner.
    WorkerPositionRequest
    Implements the message to ask a player the start position of specified worker among the available ones.
    WorkerPositionResponse
    Implements the message used to answer to the worker position request by sending the X and Y coordinate on the board.
